## Code Standards

- Functions < 30 lines, single responsibility
- Type hints everywhere
- Named constants, no magic values
- No print/console.log in production — use logging
- DRY after 2 repetitions
- Tests: `test_[what]_[condition]_[expected]`
- Comments ABOVE the line, NEVER inline. Applies to ALL files: code, config, .env, .gitignore, Dockerfile, Terraform, YAML, TOML. Many tools (Docker, shell) don't strip inline comments and treat them as values.

## Git

- One logical change per commit
- Never commit: secrets, .env, large data, terraform state
- Never reference Claude/AI/LLM in commits

## Agent Behavior

**Announce before acting.** Before creating/modifying files: explain the plan, ask for confirmation, wait for OK. Does not apply to reading files or read-only modes.

**Agent source of truth.** Any modification to an agent, skill, or template in this project's `.claude/agents/`, `.claude/skills/`, or `.claude/templates/` must also be replicated to the upstream source at `/home/kalou/WorkSpace/Agent_Workflow/`. The two copies must always stay in sync.

